review_comments.body:
On Fri, Apr 08, 2016 at 01:41:23AM -0700, Calle Erlandsson wrote:

> > @@ -729,3 +792,15 @@ free_choices(void)
> >     free(choices.v);
> >     free(input.string);
> >  }
> > +
> > +int
> > +isu8cont(unsigned char c)
> > +{
> > -   return (c & (0x80 | 0x40)) == 0x80;
> >   +}
> >   +
> >   +int
> >   +isu8start(unsigned char c)
> 
> Does this function return whether or not the byte is the continuation of an utf-8 character?

It returns 1 if the given byte marks the start of a UTF-8 character: the
two MSBs are both set to 1 as opposed of a continuation byte where the
two MSBs are equal to `10'.

